items.name: Taiga Aisaka LoRA [72MB]
items.description:
Taiga Aisaka LoRA from Toradora.

Primarily focused on getting the face accurate, but is able to get some of her outfits throughout the show. Easy to create images from the school age to post-graduation/adult (at least by presumption since the story becomes vague in the manga and the anime doesnt delve that far) by just altering obvious prompts that would be expected from aging...

Trained on Anything 4.0.

If you have any LoRA requests and wouldnt mind buying me a Hot Chocolate, please consider going to my page. https://www.buymeacoffee.com/JohnStinko

items.name: Daisy Ridley [Embedding]
items.description:
Another old project from my archive. I'm aware there's already another Daisy Ridley Embedding by Balbrig, but I figured the results are different enough due to differences in dataset and training settings that it warrants an upload. If you haven't tried Balbrig's embedding yet, be sure to get it as well!

The embed has been trained on SD 1.5 and works well on most 1.5 based models. When rendering full body images I recommend using inpainting. It also works well to let the AI use known information from the model by prompting for [Daisy Ridley|Koh_DaisyRidley] or [Daisy Ridley:Koh_DaisyRidley:0.8]. This allows the AI more creativity and it will get more varied outputs, it's worth trying.

If you enjoy my creations and want to support me or have a face you'd like to commission, consider supporting me on Ko-Fi or Buy Me A Coffee :)

items.name: 【Art Style】Sakimichan Style
items.description:
2023/6/1 update

Update dataset. Enhance training resolution to 1024x1024. Use new craft to retrain the model.

2023/3/31 update

Fix the compatibility problem of non-NAI-based checkpoints. Now arbitrary anime model with NAI's VAE or kl-f8-anime2 VAE can also generate good results using this LoRA, theoretically.

2023/3/19 update

Add trigger tag 'sakimichan' to improve generating probability. Reduce training epoch to reduce overfitting effect.

Introduction

A LoRA model trained with ~800 images by Sakimichan. The 784mb VAEs (NovelAI, Anythingv3, Orangemix, Counterfeit) are recommended. 0.6 ~ 0.8 weights are good. The preview images are generated using 1.5 version YesMix.

Cautions (Must Read)

  • Some preview images are generated using hires fix. Thus, if you wanna generate the preview images, pls download the original preview images and analyze them using 'PNG INFO' in webui to get all generating information.

  • The maximum of generating resolution should not exceed 1024 theoretically, otherwise extra/deformed head/limbs will be waiting for you :). Try to use 'hires fix' to prevent this problem and help to generate higher-resolution images.

  • For 784mb VAEs (NovelAI, Anythingv3, Orangemix, Counterfeit) users, make sure add '--no-half-vae' in command line of webui to prevent generating black images. See voldy's log for the details of edit method. For high-performance GPU, make sure 'medvram' and 'lowvram' mode are disabled.

items.name: Project-K (Kawai)
items.description:
Introduce:

I don't know how to introduce it, but it's been renamed several times. Project-K is an open, free to use and fine-tune AI-art model. It was created by my curiosity. Hope you will like it. Have fun! (●'◡'●).

Tips:

  • The `masterpiece` and `best quality` tags are not necessary, as it sometimes leads to contradictory results, but if it is distorted or discolored, add them now.

  • The CGF scale should be 7.5 and the step counts 28 for the best quality and best performance.

  • Use a sample photo for your idea. Interrogate DeepBooru and change the prompts to suit what you want.

  • You should use it as a supportive tool for creating works of art, and not rely on it completely.

  • Normal: Clip skip = 2.

Desires:

As it is a version made only by myself and my small associates, the model will not be perfect and may differ from what people expect. Any contributions from everyone will be respected.

Want to support me? Thank you, please help me make it better. ❤️

Do you want to sponsor computing resources for us? Thank you . Please sponsor to me on Ko-fi at https://ko-fi.com/projectk.

FAQs that I made up (might be helpful for you).

Do you have a Discord server?

  • Well... No, I'm not prepared for that. Besides, my English is not very good.

Can I use your model to make money?

  • Of course, feel free to do so. But you have to promise me not to sell my original model. If I'm mentioned in your credits, I'll be happy.

Why is your model's size 5.19 GB instead of 7.14 GB? I have OCD. Ahhhhhhh

  • Well... it relates to the EMA training process. In order to maximize cost efficiency, we needed to train a model using fp16. However, when I trained the model using d8ahazard's dreambooth, enabling fp16 with EMA resulted in such a skewed model. Boom, we have fp16 EMA and fp32 UNet.

Your model seems... not very good?

  • I admit, compared to other models, mine is quite bad. That's why your opinions and feedback are important to me. Please help me improve.

Can you help me improve the model's output quality?

  • Based on my experience, you should use Easy Negative, set Clip skip to 2, and make the Negative prompt similar to the images in the preview. You can also try using the hires fix Lantent once; it works fine on my potato computer. Lastly, use Adobe Photoshop and a bit of luck.

Can you help me add the things I want to your model?

  • Of course, please comment below. I will do it for you for free to the best of my abilities.

Is there a secret?

  • Secrets are not revealed, but you may have already figured it out. Bro, we're quite similar =))).

Of course, there are more questions. Comment below, and I'll answer you or someone else will. Good luck.

Special Thanks: This wouldn't have happened if they hadn't made a breakthrough.

  • Runwayml: Base model.

  • CompVis: VAE Trainer.

  • stabilityai: stabilityai/sd-vae-ft-mse-original · Hugging Face

  • d8ahazard: Dreambooth.

  • Automatic1111: Web UI.

  • Mikubill: Where my ideas started.

  • Chat-GPT: Help me do crazy things I never thought I would.

  • Novel AI, Anything Model, Abyss Orange Model, CentusMix Model, Grapefruit Model: Dataset images. An AI made me thousands of pictures without worrying about copyright or dispute.

  • Danbooru: Help me write the correct tag.

  • My friend and others: Get quality images.

  • And You 🫵❤️

Copyright:

This license allows anyone to copy, and modify the model, but please follow the terms of the CreativeML Open RAIL-M. You can learn more about the CreativeML Open RAIL-M here.

If any part of the model does not comply with the terms of the CreativeML Open RAIL-M, the copyright and other rights of the model will still be valid.

All AI-generated images are yours, you can do whatever you want, but please obey the laws of your country. We will not be responsible for any problems you cause.

Don't forget me.

Have fun with your waifu! (●'◡'●)

I'm not sure if you've read this section, but if you're wondering, "Where are versions 1.0 and 2.0? What happened to them?" Well, don't fret, they've been retired because they were about as effective as a chocolate teapot. I wouldn't want you to waste your time downloading something that's about as useful as a screen door on a submarine.

This model has a bit of a past... it's kind of hard to describe, it's like a mix of comedy and melancholy. I usually call it the "awkward situations" mode. It was trained on an utterly illogical system, an RTX 3050, yes, you heard that right, an RTX 3050. Its speed is, well, let's just say it makes snails look fast. Training for one epoch takes a whopping 4 hours, OMG. And the results? Utterly disastrous. Sometimes, I question why I'm doing this when I could be downloading something better made by someone else. Yet here I am, still at it, up until now.

Simply put, it's all for the thrill, the sensation of creating something, even if it's hilariously terrible. It's like making a lopsided cake and still being proud of it. So, if you're like me, here's a piece of advice: "Where there's a will, there's a way," so keep on truckin' in your career.

items.name: Female SciFi - AutoPrompt - Awesome prompt lists
items.description:
Description

Sci-fi themed prompt lists generated from multiple curated datasets.

Useful for when you want to create images and later go through and pick out the best creations. These prompts are randomly generated every time I generate new lists.

I use them in conjunction with a stable diffusion image viewer I have written where I view thousands of images I've created to find:

  1. Good prompts that have an art style I like

  2. Good prompts that create really good images

  3. Good compositions

Usage

  1. Open automatic1111 SD / any other SD creation tool with similar prompt file input

  2. Select <Script> --> Prompts from file or textbox

  3. Drop file or copy paste contents in the "List of prompts inputs"

  4. To view information on images you have created you can use "PNG Info" tab in Automatic1111.

Dataset description

  • Combination list contains prompts from both lists

  • Example prompt for scifi_outfit_image: Android-inspired jumpsuit with built-in holographic interface, Madam, Average Height, in shape, Heart-Shaped Face, Olive Skin, White Hair, dark brown Eyes, Long Nose, Thin Lips, Sharp Chin, Long Hair, Wavy Hair, Waterfall Braid, perky breasts, Stud earrings, black metallic lipstick, City floating in the clouds

items.name: Satono Crown - Umamusume Pretty Deby
items.description:
导言

这是一个《Umamusume Pretty Deby》《闪耀优俊少女》的里见皇冠角色LyCORIS，目前在AOM3A3上测试良好。建议以0.6左右的权重使用。在使用中使用cut off插件（https://github.com/hnmr293/sd-webui-cutoff）防止元素污染会获得更好的效果。

训练细节

以NAI Final作为底模训练，使用了46张图片作为训练集，将约一半图片作为回归训练集，每张图片重复训练10次，训练10个epoch，最终步数为900步，以下为主要设置参数：

注意没有镜像增强，因为镜像增强可能对单边的发饰绘画产生影响。

network_dim=32

network_alpha=32

keep_tokens=4

conv_dim=4

conv_alpha=4

lr="1e-4"

unet_lr="1e-4"

text_encoder_lr="1e-5"

batch_size = 2

Introduction

This is character LyCORIS of Satono Crown from "Umamusume Pretty Deby". Works well on AOM3A3. I recommend use it in a weight of around 0.6. Using the cut off extension (https://github.com/hnmr293/sd-webui-cutoff) to prevent element contamination in generation can achieve better results.

Training Details

Using NAI Final as the base model for training, 46 images were used as the training set, and about half of the images were used as the regression training set. Each image was repeatedly trained 10 times, training 10 epochs, and the final number of steps was 900. The following are the main setting parameters:

Note that there is no mirror enhancement, as mirror enhancement may have an impact on hair ornament painting.

network_ dim=32

network_ alpha=32

keep_ tokens=4

conv_ dim=4

conv_ alpha=4

lr="1e-4"

unet_ lr="1e-4"

text_ encoder_ lr="1e-5"

batch_ size = 2

items.name: Magical Interior Style: Hobbit inspired living rooms, kitchens, bathrooms and more
items.description:
What can I create with this?

Hobbit house-inspired interiors, with large windows, nice views, luxury furniture, and dark wood and leather material.

Quick Example

Positive prompt

(Professional 3D rendering:1.3) of (Ultrarealistic:1.3) magicalinterior style, bathroom, bathing room, plant, scenery, window, tree, nature, bathtub, forest, mirror, bath, faucet, water, house interior, indoors, cottage interior, treehouse interior, dark, gothic, Goth, luxury, fantasy, magic, Harry Potter, Slytherin, perfect composition, award-winning,CGSociety,ArtStation

Negative prompt

ng_deepnegative_v1_75t, bad-artist, (worst quality, low quality:1.4), multiple views, multiple panels, blurry, watermark, letterbox, text, character, human, people, 1girl, 1boy,((Wireframe)),Polygons,Screenshot,Character design,Software,UI,watermark,signature

Example Settings

768x512 px canvas size, CFG scale 7 and 70 steps on Deliberate.

Complete workflow

Prompt structure

[your medium], magicalinterior style, [Subject], [Descriptors]

Medium

You can use "professional 3d rendering" or set Image Type to Random in StylePile (highly recommended extension).

Subject

Use one of these subjects or copy-paste them to the [X] field of Style Pile and use [X] in your prompt formula instead of [Subject]. You can also generate your original subjects in ChatGTP, using the workflow described here.

kitchen, kitchen decor, kitchen design, window, scenery, plant, table, bottle, sunlight, chair

bathroom, bathing room, plant, scenery, window, tree, nature, bathtub, forest, mirror, bath, faucet, water

living room, livingroom, plant, candle, window, scenery, couch, table, candlestand, cup, potted plant, teapot, sleeping, chair, stained glass

potions lair, candle, city, scenery, window, fantasy, witchcraft, alchemy, alchemist lab, candlestand, bottle, chandelier, table, shelf

library, no scenery, books, bookshelf, window, plant, tree, lamp, table, candle, flower, chair

Descriptors

The last part of the positive prompt is descriptive tags. Use one of these or make your own:

house interior, indoors, cottage interior, treehouse interior, dark, gothic, Goth, luxury, fantasy, magic, Harry Potter, Slytherin, Lord of the rings, LOTR

house interior, indoors, cottage interior, treehouse interior, light, bright, luxury, fantasy, magic, Harry Potter, Slytherin, perfect composition, award-winning

house interior, indoors, cottage interior, treehouse interior, dark, gothic, Goth, luxury, fantasy, magic, Harry Potter, Slytherin, perfect composition, award-winning, Dirk Crabeth, unreal engine 5 highly rendered, a detailed matte painting, gothic art

Negative prompt

Use two of your favorite negative embeddings (in my case Deep Negative and Bad Artist) plus negative words from the model you are using. My case:

ng_deepnegative_v1_75t, bad-artist, (worst quality, low quality:1.4), multiple views, multiple panels, blurry, watermark, letterbox, text, character, human, people, 1girl, 1boy

Recommended models

Good results on Deliberate, The Allys Mix III, and Surreal Steampunk AI (without trigger words). Style fails to deliver with Anime models, such as Grapefruit.

Upscaling

Examples are not upscaled but you can do it with a denoising of 0.2 and your favorite upscaler in IMG2IMG.

items.name: TTP - The Tentacle Project
items.description:
NOTE: Please read the version differences before you choose the model for your download.

This model is a merge mix of many different models (no merge weights greater than 15%), with a strong emphasis on semi-realistic characters - and of course tentacles.

Unfortunately there have been many good attempts at this by others - but none have satisfied my own tentacle fetish, so I decided to make my own.

And I have to admit as of right now I am satisfied with the results my build provides. I hope you are as well.

This model is weighed heavily on strong negative prompting (listing what you don't want) , and simple prompting on what you do want.

I would suggest using the standard VAE: vae-ft-mse-84000-ema-pruned, as well as using the newer UniPC sampler. Upscale results are good with RealESRGAN_x4plus at 4x - but may achieve even better results with a better trained up-scaler.

It is also very important that I note : all of the images I offered as examples had zero inpainting nor editing done to them. Straight out of the box results, which is what I ultimately was trying to achieve.

The negative prompt that I use frequently is:


(worst quality, low quality), extra digits, text, signature, bad anatomy, mutated hand, error, missing finger, cropped, worse quality, bad quality, lowres, floating limbs, bad hands, extra legs, extra arms, random body parts, anatomical nonsense, neko ears, missing arms, missing legs, extra ears, tongue, hat, elf ears, extra hands, hands with no body, floating hands, penis with no body, amputee legs, amputee arms, extra bellybutton, pubic hairs, puffy vagina, puffy pussy, badly drawn mouth, badly drawn eyes, badly drawn pussy, badly drawn nose, badly drawn lips, body out of frame, poor facial features, bad composition, mutated body parts, disfigured, error, jpeg artifacts, malformed limbs, fused fingers, too many fingers

modelVersions.name: v2 FP32
modelVersions.description:
This is model version v2.0 FP32 full version of The Tentacle Project.

Two of the biggest difference between v1.0 and v2.0 is: 1) artifact cleanup from removal of several dirty models that I used in the original release, and 2) more emphasis on realism vs. semi-realism.

The greatest difficulty in making the model more realistic? Tentacles are not real (DOH).. And until AI advances some (or someone trains a model that outweighs this one) - this is about as best as it's going to get IMHO.

As a friendly reminder - if your rig can handle the larger FP32 unpruned model (this one), I highly highly suggest using it instead of the FP16 model. It is more textual friendly, and not as needy for negative prompting as the pruned version.

modelVersions.name: v1.0 Fp16 pruned
modelVersions.description:
Pruned Fp16 model of original.

Understand some rigs cannot handle the larger and tuned Fp32 model so I created a smaller version of the original. Still has tentacles, still does a decent job at simplified text requests, but far more artifacts and not as text savvy as the Fp32 version (cut file means cut in image quality). Nothing that inpainting cannot correct however.

As with any pictures I have produced, I use no inpainting so that you can see the quality that comes out of the model - right out of the box.

If your rig can handle the original Fp32 version, I highly recommend that over this. The only way that the Fp16 version 1.0 will get any better is if the entire model is retrained from scratch.

items.name: Color Box Model
items.description:
Color Box Model —— Providing you with a premium color experience

Trained by @YozoRaAru

Color Box is a model that emphasizes color. However, it has one drawback - not very good at drawing hands. Therefore, I recommend using it to create more visually stunning and aesthetically pleasing images. It does not require too many negative keywords to achieve excellent visual effects. I suggest trying to use only EasyNegative. Similarly, it does not need lengthy positive keywords such as masterpiece. You can simply write what you want to see in the image.

items.name: [ChumpyChoo] Chara (Undertale) LoRA
items.description:
This is a custom LoRA model for the character Chara from the popular video game Undertale. I trained the model using 79 high-quality images and utilized the AbyssOrangeMix3 model.

For optimal results, I recommend using the Euler a sampler, with the following recommended parameters:

  • CFG scale of 7

  • 20 steps

  • hires upscaler set to Latent (nearest-exact)

  • 20 hires steps

  • Denoising strength of 0.52

For optimal performance, it is recommended that the weight of the LoRA be set within the range of 0.6-0.8.

To accurately depict Chara's appearance, I suggest including knife, red eyes, and evil smile in the positive prompt. Additionally, to ensure the correct number of stripes on Chara's shirt, I recommend placing two single stripe in the positive prompt and two stripes in the negative prompt.

It should be noted that this model has a tendency to add black backgrounds in image. To mitigate this, I suggest including tags like outside,inside, anddetailed background in the positive prompt. Also put black backgroundin the negative prompt.

Please feel free to leave a comment below if you have any requests for LoRA models.

Honda Civic (sixth generation)

For the high-performance variant, see Honda Civic Type R § EK9.

Introduced in September 1995 for the 1996 model year, the sixth-generation featured updated styling although less radical than previous redesigns. Suspension and engine options were available along with their first Natural Gas Powered Civic, the GX. In the United States, model year 1996 to 2000 the Civic was sold under the CX, DX, EX, EXR, HX, LX, and for Canada, SE, and Si trims; all base models were made with 1.6-liter 4-cylinder engines. The EX-CX are all SOHC (Honda D engine). The CX, DX and LX all have SOHC (D16Y7) 4-cylinder engines; whereas the EX has a 1.6L 16-valve SOHC VTEC (D16Y8) engine producing 127 hp (95 kW), and the HX has a D16Y5 VTEC-E engine producing 115 hp (86 kW). The USDM Si and Canadian SiR came with a 1.6L 16-valve DOHC VTEC (B16A2) engine producing 160 hp (119 kW). The first Civic Si coupe EM1 was introduced in 1999 and was produced until 2000. Europe saw a DOHC 1.6 VTi hatchback and sedan and a DOHC 1.8L engine was available for the Domani related 5-door liftback and estate. In Canada, the Acura EL is based on the Civic, and was replaced by the CSX in 2006.

====================================

这个lora主要用于生成由国牌达芙妮设计的一种方头款式过膝长靴，

“方糖”这两年在睿站舞蹈区和小某书上面有多火就不用我多说了吧。

我从前几次失败的lora训练中汲取了一些教训，所以这次的发布版一上来就可以用，没有画风污染，没有面部问题（立flag呢）。无论二次元还是写实都挺好用的。（大嘘）

【国人特供の避雷点&解决方法】

1.可能是因为用novelai做底模训练的缘故，二次元情况下，大概率会出现古早的肢体问题，比如三条腿或者大腿和靴筒位置对不上，站姿基本无问题。

【解】

一、多试不同结点。

二、减少稀奇古怪的角度和姿势，dynamic angle之类的少用。

三、试试各类negative的embedding比如EasyNagtive之类的。

四、用controlnet插件。

五、忍着，然后用inpainting修复抹除。

2.在写实情况下，画面比例尽量拉长，否则要么没有下半截靴子，要么全身照会侏儒化，看着很是怪异。

【解】

一、拉长图像生成比例

二、多试试不同的checkpoint，chilloutmix的比例问题比二次元风的要多。

三、用controlnet插件，openpose可以很好的解决这个问题，唯一注意点是腿部骨骼离画面边缘不要太近，否则厚底鞋很有可能会只露半个鞋头。

四、（YYDZ，鉴定为纯纯的猜想）狡猾的小某书崽种手机摄影家们都喜欢干什么事情来让照片里的模特显腿长？没错！【P图拉腿】、【低角度拍摄】和【广角镜头畸变拉腿】视觉欺骗三件套。

所以相对应的，你可以：

①用某图秀秀后期拉腿P图

②加上prompt“from below”

③加上prompt“wide shot”

3.和一些同时带衣服特征的lora一起用的时候依然会崩崩崩，比如c站的两个蛇喰梦子lora，我每次和它们并用都会出一堆2.05D的鬼图（捶地），但是和一些真人脸模一起用就没辣么大的问题，所以我也不清楚这锅归哪边。

【解】

一、尽量只找脸模，不用一体模。

二、原生脸加prompt微调大法

三、降低权重，摁调说不定能有个平衡值。

想要改进请自取哈，别客气。

另外，给点review啊各位！秋梨膏！

items.description:
LoRA for the Tyler Sisters from Yu-Gi-Oh! Arc-V.

Surprised nobody uploaded this yet, so went ahead and made one. It turned out well I think. I trained it with 195 pictures in which in which about 175 were screencaps I manually took and edited and the rest was a few fan drawings. I took and edited it at 20 epochs with a dim/alpha of 64/32.

Triggers:

To trigger the character "Grace Tyler" just input the following after the LoRA : Grace Tyler, white hair, yellow eyes, 1girl, solo

To trigger the character "Gloria Tyler" just input the following after the LoRA : Gloria Tyler, blonde hair, pink eyes, 1girl, solo

To trigger both girls in one picture just input both triggers above except replace "1girl, solo" with "2girls, multiple girls".

Notes:

  • My experience has shown scale 0.5 ~ 0.95 work best; my best results were 0.65.

  • My prompt order shown in the sample pictures worked best for me.

  • Works on different models though weights may need to change for good results. Refer to the last two pictures in which the NeverEnding Dream (NED) and MeinaMix models were used.

  • I used FoxyaNSFW model for most of the pictures and it could give me a wide variety of styles.

  • Refer to my pictures for examples and what upscaler I used, keep in mind I have used other textual inversions to help with poses and negatives.

  • Even though the training data was nearly 95% safe for work, it can give nsfw without forcing it. If you want to use this for sfw, remember to put nsfw in negative prompts etc.

  • Works very well when creating a picture of each girl, but does struggle when creating a picture with both in the same frame. Their eye colours often get switched for some reason. Easy solution is to inpaint over the wrong coloured eyes and simply prompt for the eye colours you want.

~ ~ Spunk yes ;) ~ ~

items.name: Spartans - Halo
items.description:
The spartans from Halo!

This is a lora trained on 65 hand picked images of the spartans from Halo. It was mostly trained on digital art, with a few 3d images for variety. It was trained on various different suits and helmet types, so results have a lot of variety. It was mostly trained on female spartans, but can do male spartans just as well. It was trained on danbooru-style tags, so use those when trying to prompt - I've included the tags in a .txt file in the "Training Images" download below.

It works pretty well with most ckpts, but I recommend Anything 4.5, I used it for most of the example images.

NOTES:

-The helmet can be removed if you prompt no helmet, define the facial features, and lower the weight. It wasn't trained on any spartan with their helmets off, however.

-It will still have issues generating guns/weapons, but it can still kind of work on some models if you're lucky

-It wasn't trained on any specific spartans, but it can generate a dollar-store version of Master Chief if you prompt it right

Example prompt: (See example images, all images should still have their metadata. Just drag the images onto the PNG info tab and import it.)
